[3] World: Ebola virus still a global threat
Date: Sun 28 Dec 2014
Source: Huffington Post [edited]
http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2014/12/28/ebola-ron-klain_n_6387194.html


White House Ebola Czar Ron Klain warned Sunday [28 Dec 2014] that the virus is still a global threat and will continue to be until it is completely wiped out.

"This won't be done until we get all the way to zero," Klain said on CBS's "Face the Nation." He said the United States has made "significant strides" to prepare for the occasional case of Ebola, but West Africa is still struggling with its outbreak.

While Liberia has reduced new cases of Ebola from 50-100 a day to 5-10 a day, Sierra Leone and Guinea aren't having the same success.

[Byline: Jennifer Bendery]

