[4] Suspected, monitored, quarantined, prevention

29 Dec 2014 Japan: (Tokyo): false alarm ex West Africa
http://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2014/12/29/national/tokyo-man-tested-possible-ebola-infection/

29 Dec 2014 Japan: stock market affected by Ebola scare
http://www.thestar.com.my/Business/Business-News/2014/12/29/Nikkei-surrenders-early-gains-on-Ebola-scare/?style=biz

The Nikkei 225 fell 0.5 percent to 17 729.8 points on news that a man who returned to Japan from Sierra Leone on 23 Dec [2014] was suspected of contracting Ebola, the Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare said. But Ebola-related shares soared on the news.
[This individual has tested negative for Ebola, but immediate response to the news of suspicion of a possible case had a large impact on the stock market, both negative and positive. This is the 3rd suspect but negative case in Japan since Oct 2014.
